UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 459
1 AN ACT relating to standardizing real property tax bills.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 134 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) All real property tax bills shall be on a standardized form prescribed by the
6 department. The form shall incorporate blank spaces for inputting the following
7 information:
8 (a) The name, address, phone number, website, or other identifying
9 information of the sheriff or taxing district responsible for collecting the
10 tax;
11 (b) The taxpayer's name, mailing address, and account number;
12 (c) The physical address, parcel number, property description, or other
13 identifying information of the real property being taxed;
14 (d) The tax bill number;
15 (e) The assessed value and taxable value of the real property;
16 (f) Exemptions applicable to the real property;
17 (g) The name or description of each taxing district levying a property tax on the
18 real property;
19 (h) The tax rate for each taxing district levying a property tax on the real
20 property expressed in terms of the rate per one hundred dollars ($100) of
21 assessed value;
22 (i) The tax year of the assessment;
23 (j) Fees assessed on the real property;
24 (k) The due date and the total tax due, including a schedule of payment for
25 receiving a discount and for assessing penalties and interest;
26 (l) Delinquencies related to the real property;
27 (m) Memoranda or notes to the taxpayer;
Page 1 of 2
